title: Manhattan: 10th Street (West)

text:
Bleecker Street, west side, north from and including West 10th Street, to and including Charles Street. Also shown is West 10th Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Bleecker Street. Nos. 350-354 Bleecker Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of West 10th Street, are frame houses, with brick fronts. Nos. 215-219 West 10th Street, at the N.W. corner, and west of the N.W. corner of Bleecker Street, are frame houses, with brick fronts.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

Foot of West 10th Street, at the Hudson River.
The Empire Brewery & Malthouse, nos. 283-303 W. 10th St., is seen right of center.
